# pwa-shell — Workspace Context

## Role of This Project
This is the **shell host template** of the `@base` ecosystem. It is a GitHub Template Repository — all consumer projects are forks of this repo.

## Ecosystem Topology
```
e:/Projects/
  BASE/pwa-shell/        ← THIS repo — Vue 3 PWA shell, hosts mountable modules
  SHARED/packages/       ← @base/* packages published to GitHub Packages
    engine-core/         ← mount contract, EventBus, BaseModule, ShellContext
    ui/                  ← Vue 3 component library
    pwa-core/            ← service worker, offline utilities
  <project-name>/        ← forks of this repo — each builds one game project
```

## Code Placement Rules
- Reusable across projects → extract to `SHARED/packages/` and publish as `@base/*`
- Specific to this shell or a fork → stay in this repo
- New forks must copy `.cursor/rules/` from this template and update the workspace context section

## Stack
Vue 3 · TypeScript strict · Tailwind CSS · Vue Router · Pinia · Vite · Vitest
Backend: Node.js · Zod validation · layered architecture (routes → services → repositories)
Modules: `@base/engine-core` mount contract — all interactive modules implement `EngineModule`
